11: Your time is up—taste my steel!
22:
N-no... Another one is trying to break
through! Lady Memram, we must
close the gate!
25:
Not yet! Our comrades are still on
the other side...
39: Memram! Close the gate at once!
43:
It's trying to pry the gate open! This
isn't good...
54:
Stella?! Is that you? What are you
doing here?
58:
You know what—never mind. I need
your help! We have to push this
thing back to the other side.
68:
Got it.
Zekhel, we could use your help here!
73:
We did it...
Just in time, too...
77:
Mind telling me what the hell this
was all about?
91:
She's okay. The bleeding has
stopped.
99:
At long last, we meet, Stella.
Well, in person, at least.
103:
I think we could all use a bit of an
explanation right about now.
111:
Haha. When you put it that way, it
sounds kind of embarrassing,
doesn't it?
115:
I got all fired up and decided to
close off the abyss by myself... It was
going smoothly at first, but then I fell
right into the Rift.
118:
That place even warps the flow of
time. I was starting to worry I'd never
get out of there!
123:
The flow of time, you say...
Could that be what happened to
me as well?
127:
That was where we Vesta met
Master Nova.
131:
It's likely the Vesta were dragged
into the Rift around the time the
worlds began merging with each
other.
134:
After which everything was further
complicated by the presence of the
Purgers.
137:
Many of my tribe were slain by those
hideous winged monsters.
145:
It seems the entire Vesta tribe fell
into the Rift. Unfortunately, few of
them were capable of fighting—their
only choice was to go on the run.
148:
The only silver lining was that
Memram here turned out to be a
descendant in the line of Archons.
That meant I was able to confer her
a Star Relic.
156:
Hmm? I feel like you of all people
should know. Are you not Whitetail?
159:
The Archons are those of a lineage
granted special authority from
Stella herself. Much like yours, no?
162: How the hell am I supposed to know?
165:
I see. Well, anyway.
Memram's sword allows her to form
exits to and from the Rift.
169:
That's precisely what she was doing
here, while I was off acting as a bait
and diverting the robots' attention.
Great job, Memram.
174: I... merely did what I knew I had to.
179:
Not gonna lie, there was a lot of
gibberish packed in there. Alk, you'll
have to give me a crash course on
the lingo later.
182:
But basically, your people fell into... a
hole or something like that during a
shift, right?
184:
Memram got out first, then you
slowly started bringing over your
buddies.
191:
That is correct. Some of our
comrades still remain on the other
side.
196:
Will they be able to make their way
here on their own?
200:
No. The ruptures in space will just
close themselves up—unless we
have Memram and her Star Relic.
202:
Leaving the remaining Vesta on
their own would mean abandoning
them. Likely to their deaths.
211:
As far as the Guild's concerned, that
would certainly be the least
expensive way to deal with this
problem.
215:
What? I'm not saying that's what I
would do. But that doesn't
matter—it's the Guild that decides,
and I have a duty to report back to
them.
218:
Well, unless you guys quietly
dispose of me right here and now,
that is.
222: We wouldn't do something like that.
227:
You're a good kid, Stella. You've got
a good heart.
229:
I'll be heading back, then. If you
want the Guild to hear the story
from your perspective, you can feel
free to tag along.
232:
You too, Memram. I feel like things
would go a lot faster if you were
there.
238:
No. I know that you will choose to
expel the Vesta. My visit would be
meaningless.
241:
You're probably right.
Have it your way, then.
245: This place is connected to the abyss.
248:
Even if the Vesta were to disappear,
the Purgers will still be able to find a
way to get through.
251:
In fact, if the abyss keeps expanding
at its current rate, this entire world
will be subject to a purge. There's no
getting around this.
255:
They'll rain down from the skies, just
like they did before...
258:
I won't mince words—the situation is
grim. But... maybe it's not all bad.
261:
The fact that we were able to meet
is a good omen. If anything, I
actually feel quite... hopeful right
now.
264:
I'll be going off with Memram. Next
time, let's sit down and have a
proper chat, all right?
269:
Huh... You know, he's not what I
expected. I thought he'd be more...
proper and formal.
272:
Let's go, Stella. We've still got a lot
left to do.
